Task: How to kill a task that runs alongside the main program?

 <p>I have the following code where I start an Actix Web server and a queue handler task.
When I press Ctrl+C, I want both the HTTP server and the queue handler to shut down gracefully.
Currently, the HTTP server keeps running in the background if I suspend or kill the process.</p>
<pre><code>mod api;
mod app_context;
mod config;
mod errors;
mod models;
mod persistence;
mod pub_sub;
mod queue_handler;
mod vpn;

use crate::{api::server, app_context::AppContext, queue_handler::Handle};
use actix_web::rt;
